                            <li>October 26, 2024</li>
                        </ul>
                    </FluentCard>
                </FluentGridItem>
            </FluentGrid>

            <FluentButton Appearance="Appearance.Accent" Href="/applicants">
                Register Now
            </FluentButton>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Recent News -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="20">
            <h2>ðŸ“° Recent News</h2>
            <FluentDivider />

            <!-- News Item 1 -->
            <div>
                <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="8">
                    <h4>Enhanced Security Measures for 2024</h4>
                    <p style="color: gray; font-size: 0.9rem;">January 15, 2024</p>
                    <p>
                        The NBT Project has implemented enhanced security measures for the 2024 test administration. 
                        All candidates will be required to present original ID documents, and biometric verification 
                        will be used at test centers to ensure test integrity.
                    </p>
                </FluentStack>
            </div>

            <FluentDivider />

            <!-- News Item 2 -->
            <div>
                <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="8">
                    <h4>New Research Publication Available</h4>
                    <p style="color: gray; font-size: 0.9rem;">December 10, 2023</p>
                    <p>
                        CETAP has released a new research report examining the predictive validity of NBT scores 
                        for academic performance across South African universities. The report is available in 
                        the Resources section.
                    </p>
                    <FluentButton Appearance="Appearance.Accent" Href="/resources">
                        View Publication
                    </FluentButton>
                </FluentStack>
            </div>

            <FluentDivider />

            <!-- News Item 3 -->
            <div>
                <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="8">
                    <h4>Extended Test Centers for Rural Areas</h4>
                    <p style="color: gray; font-size: 0.9rem;">November 20, 2023</p>
                    <p>
                        In response to accessibility concerns, the NBT Project has expanded test center locations 
                        to include more venues in rural and remote areas. This initiative aims to reduce travel 
                        costs and improve access for all South African learners.
                    </p>
                </FluentStack>
            </div>

            <FluentDivider />

            <!-- News Item 4 -->
            <div>
                <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="8">
                    <h4>Digital Accommodations for Students with Disabilities</h4>
                    <p style="color: gray; font-size: 0.9rem;">October 5, 2023</p>
                    <p>
                        The NBT now offers enhanced digital accommodations for students with visual impairments 
                        and learning disabilities, including screen readers and extended time options. 
                        Contact us for accommodation requests.
                    </p>
                </FluentStack>
            </div>

            <FluentDivider />

            <!-- News Item 5 -->
            <div>
                <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="8">
                    <h4>Partnerships with Educational NGOs</h4>
                    <p style="color: gray; font-size: 0.9rem;">September 15, 2023</p>
                    <p>
                        CETAP has formed partnerships with several educational NGOs to provide NBT preparation 
                        workshops and fee waivers for financially disadvantaged students. Schools can contact 
                        us for more information about these programs.
                    </p>
                </FluentStack>
            </div>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- System Updates -->
